	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I took a look at the source code to 1.43.  The answer is: there is no way to work around it.  See wsnes9x.cpp.  Breakdown:
<br />
<br />WinInit() calls a local function named LoadExts().
<br />
<br />LoadExts() attempts to open/read "Valid.Ext".  If it fails, it calls a local function named MakeExtFile(), which is what's responsible for the creation of said file.
<br />
<br />There's no code to disable any of this functionality (no #ifdefs, no GUI toggle, nada) so you'd have to build your own SNES9x binary which doesn't call LoadExts().

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


